1. TRUE POSITIVE - JarFileUtils.java line 78: Classic Zip Slip vulnerability. ZipEntry.getName() flows directly to `new File(file, jeName)` without any path traversal check (no canonicalization, no startsWith check). A malicious JAR with entries like `../../etc/cron.d/evil` would write files outside the temp directory. This is the root cause vulnerability.

