7. FALSE POSITIVE - HtmlHelper.java line 29: `new File(outputDirectory, CSS_FILE_NAME)` - outputDirectory is a configuration parameter.

The core vulnerability is the Zip Slip in JarFileUtils.java that allows arbitrary file write when processing a malicious JAR file provided as a test suite. All downstream findings in Parser.java and Yaml.java are part of the same attack chain originating from the JarFileUtils vulnerability. The SuiteRunner/SuiteHTMLReporter/Utils findings are false positives as they deal with configured output directories, not attacker-controlled paths.

